# Delivery Sync — Product Overview

> A complete project delivery intelligence platform that gives every stakeholder — from team members to the CEO — exactly the visibility they need to ship on time.

---

## What Is Delivery Sync?

Delivery Sync is a web-based project delivery management platform built for modern software and service delivery teams. It centralises everything that typically lives across spreadsheets, chat messages, and status-update emails — standups, blockers, milestones, risks, decisions, and team activity — into one intelligent workspace.

On top of that foundation, it layers a full AI insights engine that turns your delivery data into actionable intelligence: health scores, risk alerts, trend analysis, sprint retrospectives, and a conversational query interface that lets any stakeholder ask natural-language questions about their projects.

**Built on:** Zoho Catalyst (serverless backend, datastore, cron jobs) · React + TypeScript (frontend) · Qwen 30B LLM (AI engine via Zoho QuickML)

---

## Who Is It For?

Delivery Sync is designed for organisations running one or more delivery projects simultaneously — software product companies, IT service firms, consulting agencies, and enterprise PMO teams.

| Role | What They Get |
|---|---|
| **CEO / Exec** | Portfolio health at a glance, risk intelligence, AI executive brief, strategic recommendations |
| **CTO** | Technical delivery status, blocker breakdown by severity, milestone pipeline, AI analysis |
| **PMO / Portfolio Manager** | Cross-project oversight, RAID register, decisions log, reports, standup compliance rates |
| **Delivery Lead** | Full project control — milestones, actions, blockers, team standups, AI coaching |
| **Team Member** | Submit standups & EODs, track own actions, raise blockers, personal AI performance view |
| **Client** | Read-only window into their project — milestones, reports, shareable links |

---

## Core Modules

### 1. Projects
Create and manage multiple projects simultaneously. Each project has a RAG (Red / Amber / Green) health status that is updated by leads and surfaced automatically in all dashboards.

- Track project start and end dates
- Assign team members with specific project roles (Tech Lead, Developer, Scrum Master, Designer, QA, etc.)
- Monitor overall progress through integrated milestones, actions, and blockers
- RAG status changes are logged for audit purposes

---

### 2. Milestones
Define the key delivery checkpoints for each project and track them through to completion.

- Set milestones with due dates and descriptions
- Statuses: Pending → In Progress → Completed / Delayed
- Overdue milestones are automatically surfaced in dashboards and executive views
- Milestone completion rates appear in AI health scoring

---

### 3. Daily Updates — Standup & EOD
Replace scattered chat messages and email threads with structured daily updates.

**Daily Standup:**
- What did I work on yesterday?
- What am I working on today?
- Any blockers?

**End-of-Day (EOD):**
- What did I accomplish today?
- What's planned for tomorrow?
- Mood / energy level

These entries feed directly into the AI engine, enabling blocker detection, trend analysis, and performance insights. Automated reminders are sent to ensure team compliance.

---

### 4. Actions
A lightweight action-item tracker that keeps accountability clear across the entire project.

- Create actions with due dates, assignees, and priority levels
- Statuses: Open → In Progress → Done / Cancelled
- Overdue actions are escalated in dashboards and AI analysis
- Actions link to projects for portfolio-level visibility

---

### 5. Blockers
A dedicated module to raise, track, and resolve anything that is stopping progress.

- Four severity levels: Critical · High · Medium · Low
- Statuses: Open → In Progress → Escalated → Resolved
- Blockers that remain open beyond 3 days are automatically escalated
- Critical and High blockers surface prominently in the CEO and CTO dashboards
- AI Blocker Detection can identify implicit blockers from standup and EOD text — things teams mention in passing but have not formally raised

---

### 6. RAID Register
A complete Risk, Assumption, Issue, and Dependency log for projects.

| Type | What It Tracks |
|---|---|
| **Risks** | Potential threats with probability and impact ratings |
| **Issues** | Problems that are actively happening |
| **Dependencies** | Internal and external dependencies with status tracking |
| **Assumptions** | Project assumptions that can be validated or invalidated |

Each RAID item has its own status lifecycle. Unresolved items are visible in executive dashboards and AI risk analysis.

---

### 7. Decisions
Never lose track of a key project decision again. The Decisions log captures what was decided, when, and by whom — making retrospectives and audits straightforward.

- Log decisions with context and rationale
- Statuses: Open → Implemented → Reversed
- Decision counts appear in executive dashboards
- Fully audited — every change is recorded

---

### 8. Teams
Organise your people into named teams with clear roles and membership.

- Create teams with leads and members
- Assign team roles (Scrum Master, Product Owner, Tech Lead, Developer, Designer, QA, DevOps, Business Analyst, and more)
- Team composition is visible in all reporting
- Team size and structure feed into AI recommendations

---

### 9. Reports
Generate, view, and share structured reports without manual effort.

**Report types available:**
- **Weekly Report** — Rolling seven-day delivery summary
- **Monthly Report** — Monthly delivery performance
- **Custom Range** — Any date range you need
- **Daily Summary** — Single-day digest
- **User Performance** — Individual contributor metrics
- **Team Performance** — Aggregate team metrics
- **Project Summary** — Full project health and delivery status

**Public sharing:** Every report can be shared via a unique public link — no login required for the recipient. Perfect for sharing progress with clients or leadership without giving them system access.

---

## Dashboards

### General Dashboard
The first screen every user sees on login. Tailored to their role — team members see their own work, leads see their projects, executives see the portfolio.

### Portfolio Dashboard
A cross-project health matrix for PMO and executive roles. Aggregated view of all active projects, their RAG statuses, and key delivery metrics.

### CEO Dashboard
Business-focused executive intelligence. Built for a CEO who needs the full picture in one view.

**What it shows:**
- Portfolio health score (composite metric)
- Active projects vs. completed vs. on hold
- Open risks and critical blockers count
- Overdue actions count
- Team velocity (standup submission rate)
- RAG breakdown donut chart
- Team activity trend (last 7 days)
- Milestone progress by project (bar chart)
- Full project portfolio table with health scores
- Critical and high blockers list
- Delivery metrics grid

**AI Executive Brief (4-source intelligence):**
The CEO dashboard's AI brief aggregates output from four simultaneous AI analyses:
1. Portfolio health status with reasons and risk flags
2. Detected delivery blockers with severity and resolution suggestions
3. Team pulse — productivity, engagement, and mood trends
4. Risk mitigation and strategic recommendations, resource allocation suggestions, immediate actions required

Everything a CEO needs to walk into a board meeting or a delivery review — generated in one click.

### CTO Dashboard
Technical and delivery-focused intelligence for engineering and delivery leadership.

**What it shows:**
- Active projects and critical blocker counts
- Overdue actions and delayed milestones
- Sprint health score
- Open risks count
- Project health bar chart (health score vs. milestone progress)
- Blocker severity breakdown (pie chart)
- Team velocity line chart (7-day trend)
- Filterable project health table with RAG, health scores, milestone progress, overdue counts, and end-date countdown
- Delivery pipeline — upcoming milestones (7 days) and overdue milestones
- Active blockers list with severity and raised date
- AI Delivery Analysis — detected blockers with root causes, trend insights, portfolio health summary

---

## AI Insights Engine

Delivery Sync includes a dedicated AI service powered by a 30-billion-parameter language model. It reads your actual delivery data — standups, EODs, actions, blockers, milestones — and generates human-readable intelligence.

### Available AI Analyses

| Feature | What It Does |
|---|---|
| **Daily Summary** | Summarises what the team accomplished, highlights key activities, detects sentiment |
| **Project Health** | Classifies each project as On Track / At Risk / Delayed with specific reasons and a health score |
| **Performance Analysis** | Per-member performance insights, strengths, and improvement areas over a configurable window |
| **AI Report Generation** | Fully written daily, weekly, or project reports with executive summaries |
| **Smart Suggestions** | Prioritised suggestions across three dimensions: productivity, risk mitigation, and resource allocation |
| **Blocker Detection** | Scans standup and EOD text to find both explicit and implicit blockers your team mentioned but did not formally raise |
| **Trend Analysis** | Identifies productivity, engagement, and mood trends across 7 to 90 days with predictions |
| **Sprint Retrospective** | Generates a structured retrospective: what went well, what went wrong, action items, velocity score, key learnings |
| **Natural Language Query** | Ask any question in plain English — "Which projects are at risk this week?" — and get a direct answer |

### Role-Scoped AI
AI results are automatically scoped to what each user is allowed to see:
- **Admin / PMO / Exec** — Full tenant-wide analysis
- **Delivery Lead** — Their projects
- **Team Member** — Their own activity and assigned work
- **Client** — Their assigned project only

---

## Automation & Notifications

Delivery Sync runs several automated background processes so nothing falls through the cracks.

| Automation | What It Does |
|---|---|
| **Standup Reminder** | Daily reminder sent to all team members to submit their standup |
| **EOD Reminder** | Evening reminder to submit end-of-day updates |
| **Overdue Action Alert** | Notifies owners when their actions become overdue |
| **Blocker Escalation** | Automatically escalates blockers that have been open for 3+ days |
| **Daily Summary** | Generates and delivers an automated daily delivery digest |

**11 notification types** are supported, covering task assignments, blocker additions, project assignments, team updates, report readiness, and more.

---

## Access Control & Security

### Six User Roles
Every user is assigned one of six tenant roles, each with precisely scoped permissions:

| Role | Description |
|---|---|
| **Tenant Admin** | Full system access — all features, admin panel, user management, audit logs |
| **PMO** | Portfolio and reporting focus — full read/write on projects, RAID, decisions, milestones |
| **Delivery Lead** | Project execution focus — full access to own projects, can invite team members |
| **Team Member** | Contributor access — standups, EODs, own actions, raise blockers |
| **Exec** | Read-only view of everything — executive dashboards, reports, aggregate metrics |
| **Client** | External access — project milestones, reports, public share links only |

### 25 Granular Permissions
Under the hood, access is enforced through 25 individual permission flags covering every API endpoint. This means you can be confident that a Client user will never see internal standup details, a Team Member can never modify project settings, and an Exec can view everything without accidentally editing anything.

### Audit Trail
Every create, update, delete, status change, role change, escalation, and notification is written to an immutable audit log. Full traceability for compliance and accountability.

---

## Multi-Tenant Architecture

Delivery Sync is fully multi-tenant. Each organisation (tenant) operates in complete isolation:
- Separate data namespaces
- Unique URL slug per organisation (`/your-company/dashboard`)
- Independent user bases and role assignments
- Super Admin panel for platform-level tenant management

---

## Key Benefits for Your Organisation

**Visibility** — Everyone from a junior developer to the CEO sees the information relevant to their role in real time. No more "can you send me a status update" messages.

**Accountability** — Actions, blockers, and milestones have owners and due dates. Automated reminders and escalations mean nothing goes untracked.

**Early Warning System** — The combination of RAG status tracking, blocker severity levels, overdue milestone alerts, and AI analysis means problems surface days earlier than in manual processes.

**AI That Works With Your Data** — The AI engine does not generate generic advice. It reads your team's actual standups, EODs, and project data and returns insights specific to your delivery context.

**Client Confidence** — Share polished, always-current project reports with clients via a simple link — no login required. Keep clients informed without giving them access to internal discussions.

**Reduced Meetings** — Structured standups, EODs, automated summaries, and AI briefings dramatically reduce the need for status-check meetings. The data is already there.

**Audit-Ready** — Every action in the system is logged. Whether for internal governance, client SLAs, or compliance requirements, you have a complete record.

